'''Caspian International Petroleum Company (CIPCO)''' ([[Azerbaijani language|Azerbaijani]]: ''Xəzər Beynəlxalq Neft Şirkəti'') was a joint operating company established by production shareholding companies for exploration, development and production sharing of the [[Karabakh (Oil and Gas field)|Karabakh]] field in the section of the [[Caspian Sea]] within [[Azerbaijan]].
==History== It was incorporated on 4 June 1996. The company was led by President James A. Tilley, who had been the President of ''[[Pennzoil]] Caspian''.<ref name="Azerbaijan International"> {{cite journal | url = http://azer.com/aiweb/categories/magazine/43_folder/43_articles/43_caspian.html | title = Caspian International Petroleum Company. Formed for Exploration, Development of Karabakh Prospect |date=Autumn 1996 | journal = [[Azerbaijan International]] | accessdate = 2009-12-08 }} </ref>
Shareholders of CIPCO had the following stakes in Karabakh field: {| class=wikitable !Company !Interest |- |[[LUKAgip]] [[Joint venture|JV]] |45% |- |[[Pennzoil]] |30% |- |[[LUKOIL]] |12.5% |- |[[SOCAR]] |7.5% |- |[[Agip]] |5% |}
===Feasibility studies=== The company estimated an investment of up to $2 billion, if the feasibility studies proved the expectations for reserves.<ref name="Azerbaijan International-2"> {{cite journal | url = http://azer.com/aiweb/categories/magazine/44_folder/44_articles/44_socar_cipco.html | title = CIPCO. Developing the Karabakh Prospect | author = James Tilley |date=Winter 1996 | journal = [[Azerbaijan International]] | accessdate = 2009-12-08 }} </ref> CIPCO spent nearly $100 million on feasibility studies.<ref name=Nefte.ru>[http://www.nefte.ru/projekt/s6.htm ''НЕФТЕГАЗОДОБЫЧА В СТРАНАХ СНГ'']</ref>
;Closure In January 1999, the consortium management announced the project was not commercially feasible and as of 23 February 1999 it stopped its operations and was dissolved.<ref> {{cite news | url= http://www.gasandoil.com/goc/company/cnc91019.htm | title= CIPCO dissolved | publisher= Alexander's Gas & Oil Connections | volume = 4 | issue = 4 | date=1999-03-03 | accessdate=2009-12-08 }}</ref>
