'''Jorge Camil Starr''' (born 1980) is a Mexican-American social entrepreneur and businessman specializing in technology, education and the environment. He is co-founder and coordinator of technology and education in Enova,<ref name="MIT 2013">[http://www.technologyreview.es/tr35mexico/profile.aspx?trid=1384 "Jorge Camil, 31"], MIT Technology Review, 2013.</ref> a social enterprise focusing on  technology and educational strategies. Jorge was recognized as an Endeavor Entrepreneur and an Ashoka Fellow in 2011.<ref>[http://www.endeavor.org/entrepreneurs/jorge-camil/978 Endeavor Entrepreneur]</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.enovamexico.com/experiencia.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2011-06-10 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100207010320/http://enovamexico.com/experiencia.html |archivedate=2010-02-07 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.takepart.com/news/2011/05/25/jorge-camil-innovates-education-in-mexco-city |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2011-06-10 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110609093401/http://www.takepart.com/news/2011/05/25/jorge-camil-innovates-education-in-mexco-city |archivedate=2011-06-09 |df= }}</ref>

He completed a double bachelor's degree in Economics and Business Administration at [[Pepperdine University]],<ref name="MIT 2013" /> in 2004, and also holds diplomas in Marketing from [[Imperial College London]] (2003); Corporate Finance, [[Instituto Tecnológico Autónomo de México]] (ITAM), 2006; Digital Governance, Tecnológico de Monterrey (ITESM), Mexico  (2007); and Senior Management in Technology and Innovation, El Instituto Panamericano de Alta Dirección de Empresa (IPADE), Mexico (2008).{{citation needed|date=July 2013}}

He was board member of IMIFAP.<ref>{{cite book| url=https://books.google.com/books?id=M-XdiudnUKQC&pg=PA283&lpg=PA283&dq=Jorge+Camil+Starr&source=bl&ots=oNKjP03IdX&sig=k-3L0XUDeWoH7XQuJUJ4klpqpUY&hl=en&ei=8ITyTeTwC9PSgQex6-zeCw&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=9&ved=0CEsQ6AEwCDgK#v=onepage&q=Jorge%20Camil%20Starr&f=false| title=Breaking the Poverty Cycle: The Human Basis for Sustainable Development| authors=Susan Pick, Jenna Sirkin| publisher=Oxford University Press | year=2010| isbn=978-0-19-538316-4 }}</ref>

He previously served as Director of PLC Networks, S.A. de C.V, a broadband over powerline company.{{Citation needed|date=June 2011}}  In 2005, Jorge co-created LT Solutions S.A. de C.V, a distributor of Ncomputing for México and Central America. {{Citation needed|date=June 2011}}

He has served as coordinator for the movement “Time for Nature 2008.”{{Citation needed|date=June 2011}} Jorge also serves as a representative volunteer for TCP, The Climate Change Project.{{Citation needed|date=June 2011}}

